1
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:41,900
<i>Why are you all dressed up?
Are you going somewhere?</i>

2
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:43,200
<i>You're going to run away
from me, aren't you?</i>

3
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:44,967
<i> Why would you think that?</i>

4
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:48,333
<i>I just want to visit
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson.</i>

5
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:52,267
<i>And how will we let you
know when you have our phones?</i>

6
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:54,267
<i>I'm giving you back
your phone because I realized</i>

7
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,667
<i>that we don't have
a means of communication.</i>

8
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:56,800
<i> I crossed the line, Felma.</i>

9
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:58,100
<i>What I did
was completely wrong.</i>

10
00:00:58,233 --> 00:00:59,733
<i> Because I was badly hurt.</i>

11
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:02,333
<i>I told you before that
I love you without a reason.</i>

12
00:01:02,467 --> 00:01:06,033
<i>But I realized now that I only
love you as a friend.</i>

13
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:07,800
<i> I deserve to know the truth.</i>

14
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:08,933
<i> Is it Manuel?</i>

15
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:10,367
<i> Do you still love him?</i>

16
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:12,833
<i>Is that why you
can only love me as a friend?</i>

17
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:14,500
<i> Hello, Jessica?</i>

18
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:17,800
<i>Dad and I are here in the
Philippines. We just arrived.</i>

19
00:01:17,933 --> 00:01:18,700
<i> Manuel!</i>

20
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,267
<i>- Friend, calm down.
- Jessica!</i>

21
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,567
<i> Where are they?</i>

22
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:24,200
<i>No wonder Manuel and Jessica
want to get away from you.</i>

23
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,300
<i>And we were right
when we helped them</i>

24
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:27,967
<i> get back to the Philippines.</i>

25
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:29,433
<i> So, Philippines?</i>

26
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:30,900
<i>I heard you talking
on the phone earlier.</i>

27
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:33,300
<i> Was it Mr. and Mrs. Wilson?</i>

28
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:34,933
<i>Dad, I was talking
to Miss Felma.</i>

29
00:01:35,067 --> 00:01:36,133
<i> Why did you call her?</i>

30
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:38,433
<i>Dad, I know that you
wanted to ask her</i>

31
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:40,467
<i> for forgiveness in person.</i>

32
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,200
<i>And I will get to meet
my siblings</i>

33
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:45,067
<i>and have a connection with them.</i>

34
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,667
<i>Is there something
bothering you?</i>

35
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,900
<i> Is it about Manuel?</i>

36
00:01:48,033 --> 00:01:52,633
<i>You only have that reaction
when it's about him.</i>

37
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:56,333
<i>I won't let Manuel pull one
over on me. I'll go home too.</i>

38
00:01:56,467 --> 00:02:01,567
<i>And I will never let him
go back to that flirty Felma!</i>

39
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:04,267
<i> I will get them back!</i>

40
00:02:08,133 --> 00:02:09,400
Hello, Pretty Mama.

41
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:11,300
Is my dad home?

42
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:14,900
Yes, we just got home.

43
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:17,233
May I talk to him, please?

44
00:02:17,367 --> 00:02:19,067
I just want to say good night.

45
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:22,367
He's still outside,
he's parking the car.

46
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:24,567
Just call him, okay?

47
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:27,133
Okay, Pretty Mama.
Love you! Good night!

48
00:02:27,267 --> 00:02:29,233
Love you too, Tetay.

49
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:45,933
Mom?

50
00:02:46,067 --> 00:02:48,167
What's the matter?

51
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:52,033
Ever since you talked
to Uncle Noah at the restaurant,

52
00:02:52,167 --> 00:02:55,167
you've always seemed
deep in thought.

53
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:58,167
Is something bothering you?

54
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,533
No.

55
00:03:01,533 --> 00:03:03,433
It's about your dad.

56
00:03:03,567 --> 00:03:04,733
What?

57
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,000
Why, Mom?

58
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:09,200
What happened to him?

59
00:03:10,467 --> 00:03:12,800
They are here.

60
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:14,633
He is here with Jessica.

61
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,233
Really? Dad is back?

62
00:03:19,367 --> 00:03:23,100
Mom, let's go see them!
I want to see them!

63
00:03:23,267 --> 00:03:24,633
Coleen!

64
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:28,333
Sorry, Mom.

65
00:03:28,467 --> 00:03:31,700
I just can't help myself

66
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,133
because I've been
longing for this.

67
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:35,433
I've been
praying for this.

68
00:03:35,567 --> 00:03:38,133
To see my dad.

69
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:42,000
Mom, don't worry.

70
00:03:42,133 --> 00:03:43,600
We will keep it a secret.

71
00:03:43,733 --> 00:03:47,033
Andrea and Jeffrey
will not find out.

72
00:04:03,533 --> 00:04:05,800
Let go of me!

73
00:04:05,933 --> 00:04:09,967
Andrea, you have to calm down.

74
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:12,300
Because if you face them
while you're angry,

75
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:14,800
you're going to cause
trouble again.

76
00:04:21,867 --> 00:04:24,000
Mom, I want to see Dad.

77
00:04:24,133 --> 00:04:26,567
Come on, let's go see him!

78
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:31,600
But I'm a bit nervous.
I don't know what to say.

79
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:34,100
You're not going
to see him!

80
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,400
What?

81
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,200
Why not?

82
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:43,833
If you don't want to see him,
then I will.

83
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:47,600
Jeffrey and Andrea
will get mad.

84
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:49,267
You will just end up fighting.

85
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,867
They can get mad at me
for all I care!

86
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,167
The problem with them is that
they want me to be mad at Dad

87
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:57,600
just because
they are mad at him.

88
00:04:58,433 --> 00:04:59,800
Coleen.

89
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:05,233
I understand how you feel.

90
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:09,433
You're longing for him,
I understand that.

91
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:17,233
But will you turn your back
on your siblings for him?

92
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:20,767
Think of your brother
and sister.

93
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:24,400
They've been with you
your whole life.

94
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:26,300
But your dad...

95
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:29,267
you haven't even met him
in person.

96
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:32,700
Mom, I just want to see
how Dad is doing.

97
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,400
I'm just worried about him.

98
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:37,767
What if he's having a hard time
because of his paralysis?

99
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:41,400
Mom, do I really have
to choose between Dad

100
00:05:41,533 --> 00:05:43,567
and my siblings?

101
00:05:44,867 --> 00:05:46,833
You shouldn't have.

102
00:05:47,233 --> 00:05:51,133
But for now, you have to choose.

103
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:54,400
It's not fair!

104
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,600
Life is not fair.

105
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,600
Let's just accept the fact

106
00:06:15,733 --> 00:06:18,667
that we all have
our own families now.

107
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,600
Even if your dad is back.

108
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:25,567
Coleen, he is no longer
a part of our lives.

109
00:06:27,467 --> 00:06:30,200
Even if we are worried
about him,

110
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:32,400
we can't do anything else.

111
00:06:34,133 --> 00:06:36,667
Let's just pray for him.

112
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:05,000
Hey, why are you crying?

113
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:11,600
Why?

114
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:14,533
What is going on?

115
00:07:17,533 --> 00:07:21,900
Coleen's dad is back here
in the Philippines.

116
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:23,433
What?

117
00:07:26,633 --> 00:07:28,967
Mom and Coleen
know about it.

118
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:32,033
They are keeping it
a secret from us.

119
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:42,000
Is he really not going
to leave us alone?

120
00:07:43,267 --> 00:07:45,467
Mom...

121
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,533
and Coleen.

122
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:50,233
Why does it seem
like nothing happened?

123
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:52,500
They seem happy
that he is here.

124
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:54,967
Am I the only one
who couldn't forget

125
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,833
what he's done to our family?

126
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,933
I can understand
how Coleen feels.

127
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:04,300
She didn't get to experience

128
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:08,433
all the pain that we went
through because of him.

129
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:10,100
But Mom...

130
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,200
Our mom!

131
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:16,667
I don't understand.

132
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:21,433
This is the reason Mom broke up
with Uncle Noah.

133
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:28,233
No matter what she says,
her ex is still the reason!

134
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:33,900
It's because of her ex-husband!

135
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:35,667
No matter what she says!

136
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:39,167
That's enough, stop it.

137
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:45,700
We're not going to let
them meet with him.

138
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:47,933
They can't meet with him!
They're not allowed to!

139
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:53,600
We're not gonna let him
ruin our lives again.

140
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:03,033
Jessica, sweetie.
Come on, let's eat.

141
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,133
I should have done that.

142
00:09:04,267 --> 00:09:05,600
Come on, sit down.

143
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:07,467
- I got this.
- Dad, let me do that.

144
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,733
Come on, I got this.

145
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:10,967
Just sit down.

146
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:13,367
- I can do this, Dad.
- Come on.

147
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:16,033
Make sure you eat a lot.
One more scoop?

148
00:09:16,167 --> 00:09:18,333
Dad, that's good enough.
Let me do it.

149
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,233
Thank you.

150
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:24,100
Go ahead, eat.

151
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:31,033
Come on, Dad.
I could have done this.

152
00:09:33,567 --> 00:09:35,200
Sweetie.

153
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:37,067
Thank you.

154
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,000
For what?

155
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:41,567
For letting me
do this for you.

156
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:44,467
You never made me feel
like I'm useless.

157
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,933
Because you're not, Dad.

158
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:48,133
I know that you can do it.

159
00:09:50,467 --> 00:09:53,133
It seems like you didn't
sleep well last night.

160
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,300
Do you feel guilty for
ignoring your mom's call?

161
00:09:57,433 --> 00:10:00,767
And you also blocked her
on your Friendsbook.

162
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:02,167
I do feel bad.

163
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:05,267
But I don't
regret it, Dad.

164
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:08,233
I know that if I don't block
her, she'll keep calling.

165
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:11,133
And she will give us
a hard time again.

166
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,333
What about you, Dad?

167
00:10:14,467 --> 00:10:17,567
It seems like you didn't
sleep well last night either.

168
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:22,567
I was just thinking
about our finances.

169
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:27,500
Even if we find a cheap
apartment, I estimate that

170
00:10:27,633 --> 00:10:30,500
our money will only
last around six months.

171
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:32,100
I'll buy a cheap
laptop, Dad.

172
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:33,800
Then I'll find
an online job.

173
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,533
What are you
talking about?

174
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:37,367
I won't let you get a job.

175
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,800
You shouldn't worry
about our finances.

176
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:42,400
Just think
about your studies.

177
00:10:42,533 --> 00:10:45,300
We need to find
a school for you.

178
00:10:45,433 --> 00:10:47,267
Dad, that can wait.

179
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:50,067
We should focus on
settling here first.

180
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:54,200
We need to be financially
stable and secure.

181
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:59,267
Sweetie,
can I borrow your phone?

182
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,333
Sure.

183
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,700
Here, Dad.

184
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:13,067
What's his number again?

185
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:15,700
09...

186
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:24,933
Hello, Abel?

187
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:32,167
I want to call Jessica.

188
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:35,333
I just want to know
how Dad is doing.

189
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:36,267
But the problem is that my mom

190
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:38,567
has forbidden me
from calling her.

191
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:41,867
She said my siblings
will get mad if they find out.

192
00:11:43,567 --> 00:11:45,267
I'll check, okay?

193
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:46,633
Alright, come what may.

194
00:11:46,767 --> 00:11:48,767
I'll call you back later.

195
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:53,900
Are you still going
to call her, Coleen?

196
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:58,300
Didn't mom already tell
you not to do that?

197
00:11:58,433 --> 00:11:59,800
What are you doing here?

198
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:02,533
- Have you been eavesdropping?
- Yes.

199
00:12:02,667 --> 00:12:04,767
Because I know
that your father is here

200
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,367
and you want to meet with him.

201
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:07,400
What...

202
00:12:07,533 --> 00:12:10,833
And you want to keep it
a secret from us.

203
00:12:10,967 --> 00:12:12,867
What was that about, Coleen?

204
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,933
How can you do this to me?

205
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:19,067
I'm your sister,
and you betrayed me?

206
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:22,467
Coleen, do you really care more
about your father than us?

207
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,133
- That's not true.
- Liar!

208
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:26,600
You want to meet
with your father

209
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:28,533
even when we didn't want you to!

210
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:31,300
I can make my own decision now,
Andrea.

211
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:32,867
I'm not a child anymore
for you to dictate

212
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,100
what I should and shouldn't do!

213
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:35,867
And I'm the only one

214
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,467
who actually wants to see Dad.

215
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,500
I'm not even involving you
in this.

216
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:43,433
Not even Mom. So please,
let me do this.

217
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:46,533
No, because if we let you go,
we don't know what kind

218
00:12:46,667 --> 00:12:49,700
of trouble that man will bring
into our lives again!

219
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:51,367
Look at what happened.

220
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:54,633
Mom and Uncle Noah
broke up because of him.

221
00:12:55,967 --> 00:12:57,333
Oh, my, Coleen.

222
00:12:57,467 --> 00:12:58,900
What do you want to happen?

223
00:12:59,033 --> 00:13:01,233
You want all of us to be
caught up in this mess?

224
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:03,933
You're so selfish, Andrea.

225
00:13:04,067 --> 00:13:06,033
I just want to get to know Dad!

226
00:13:06,167 --> 00:13:08,567
- I just want to see...
- You're the selfish one!

227
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:10,300
You never consider us!

228
00:13:10,433 --> 00:13:12,000
You only think about yourself!

229
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:13,600
That's enough.

230
00:13:14,733 --> 00:13:16,733
Coleen, just do as you're told.

231
00:13:16,867 --> 00:13:19,467
Don't contact your dad or
his daughter ever again.

232
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,133
That's right!

233
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,367
Because we'll never know
what could happen to Mom.

234
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:25,700
She could fall into
depression again.

235
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:28,233
Like last time,
when she became a drunkard.

236
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:31,467
Why are you stuck in the past?
That's over!

237
00:13:32,433 --> 00:13:35,333
Dad became paralyzed,
don't you feel bad for him?

238
00:13:35,467 --> 00:13:37,833
What about us?
Don't you feel bad for us?

239
00:13:37,967 --> 00:13:40,467
We are hurting too.

240
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:43,200
Everything that
we've been through!

241
00:13:43,767 --> 00:13:46,667
He almost ruined our lives!

242
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:50,233
I couldn't focus on my studies.
I lost my way!

243
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:53,433
And Jeffrey, he had to steal
and almost went to jail for it.

244
00:13:53,567 --> 00:13:57,567
And you, you didn't know it, but
we failed to take care of you.

245
00:13:57,733 --> 00:14:02,067
We neglected you because
we are not in our right minds.

246
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:05,267
And all of that happened
because of your father!

247
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:09,233
Do you want to live
like that again, Coleen?

248
00:14:09,367 --> 00:14:11,233
So what now, are we going to
ruin our family's peace,

249
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:14,633
especially Mom's, just because
you want to see your father?

250
00:14:14,767 --> 00:14:16,633
I'm telling you Coleen.

251
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:20,533
If you don't stop,
don't say I didn't warn you.

252
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:24,700
Because you'll lose me
as your sister.

253
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:42,667
Don't you think we were a bit
too hard on Coleen?

254
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:45,100
I feel like we were being
unfair, aren't we?

255
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:47,633
No. She needs to hear it.

256
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:51,800
She needs to know that her dad
is nothing but trouble.

257
00:14:51,933 --> 00:14:55,400
I don't know, Andrea.
We do have a point, I get that.

258
00:14:55,533 --> 00:14:58,567
But we should consider
Coleen's feelings.

259
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:00,200
She had a reason.

260
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,500
We have a valid reason
for feeling this way!

261
00:15:04,633 --> 00:15:06,567
We just don't want to
relive the nightmare her

262
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:09,167
father put us through back then.

263
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:12,067
Andrea really said that?

264
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:15,767
Yes, I want to see my dad.

265
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:18,167
But I don't want
to lose my sister.

266
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:22,100
What if she tells Mom, and tells
her we're ganging up on her?

267
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,133
She can go ahead.

268
00:15:27,267 --> 00:15:31,400
But I don't think
Coleen will do that.

269
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:33,900
She knows that Mom
doesn't like conflict.

270
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:35,567
She also knows
that it will affect her

271
00:15:35,733 --> 00:15:38,267
if she finds out
we've been fighting.

272
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:39,467
Bestie, if I were you,

273
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:42,100
I'd choose the people who've
been with me all my life

274
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:47,200
over someone
I don't even really know.

275
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:52,100
He's not just someone
else, he's my dad.

276
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:54,033
Sorry. You're right.

277
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:55,667
We're not sure about her.

278
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,100
She's from a different
generation.

279
00:15:57,233 --> 00:15:59,900
She thinks
differently from us.

280
00:16:00,033 --> 00:16:03,233
I was thinking we should
have talked to her calmly.

281
00:16:03,367 --> 00:16:04,767
She might have listened to us.

282
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,500
So, what's your plan?

283
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:08,467
I still want to see my dad.

284
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:10,200
I don't understand you.

285
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:12,567
You just said that you didn't
want to lose your sister.

286
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:15,100
They're being so
unreasonable!

287
00:16:15,233 --> 00:16:19,867
I'm already done doing
what I'm told!

288
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,367
I will fight for my rights
as our father's daughter.

289
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,833
We just did what is right.

290
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:28,767
I'm serious about what I said.

291
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:33,267
If she won't stop and become
stubborn, she'll lose a sibling!

292
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,533
A sister!

293
00:16:34,667 --> 00:16:36,867
I don't know about you.

294
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,033
Bestie, think about it.

295
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:40,667
What if they find out?

296
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,300
I will keep it a secret.

297
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:46,533
No one will know except you.

298
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:49,900
Okay, fine.

299
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:55,700
Friend! I bought dinner for us!

300
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:57,400
Thank you.

301
00:17:12,967 --> 00:17:16,533
What? One-way ticket to Manila?
Seriously?

302
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:19,000
Why didn't you get
a round-trip ticket?

303
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:21,033
Look at how much it costs.

304
00:17:21,167 --> 00:17:23,200
The price is sky-high.

305
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:26,433
There's no promo fare
because it's so sudden.

306
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:28,800
What about Niagara Airways?

307
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:32,800
They have a sale next week.
It seems good.

308
00:17:32,933 --> 00:17:35,067
I can't wait that long.

309
00:17:35,967 --> 00:17:39,267
Take care of things here.
I'll leave you the keys.

310
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,900
And then I will send you money
from Manila

311
00:17:42,033 --> 00:17:44,867
once I get there
for the mortgage payment.

312
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,467
Wait, mortgage?

313
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:51,000
So you have no plans
of coming back anytime soon?

314
00:17:51,167 --> 00:17:53,933
I'm going to a war, Alice.

315
00:17:54,067 --> 00:17:58,200
And this war
is going to be a long one.

316
00:17:59,467 --> 00:18:03,500
Oh, my, Hazel! Are you really
off to create chaos?

317
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,367
Yes.

318
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:09,033
And I will make sure that Manuel

319
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:11,800
and that pathetic mistress
of his don't come out on top.

320
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:16,300
Friend, you'll be all alone.
What are you thinking?

321
00:18:16,433 --> 00:18:18,067
So what?

322
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:21,200
I was born ready, Alice.

323
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:27,300
And mark my words.
In this war, I will win.

324
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:33,300
Uncle Abel.

325
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:35,000
- Jessica!
- Hi!

326
00:18:35,133 --> 00:18:35,933
Nice to meet you.

327
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:37,900
You've gotten so big.

328
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:40,300
Last time I saw you...

329
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:54,467
Bro.

330
00:18:56,133 --> 00:18:57,500
You look like
you're about to cry.

331
00:18:57,633 --> 00:18:59,533
Do you feel sorry for me?

332
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,033
No, idiot!

333
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:06,300
I miss you!

334
00:19:06,433 --> 00:19:08,233
Last time we saw each other,
we almost beat each other up.

335
00:19:08,367 --> 00:19:10,333
I even shoved you in a taxi,
remember?

336
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,067
You idiot!

337
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:16,267
Are you still mad at me?

338
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,167
Would I contact you
if I'm mad at you?

339
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:22,033
That's right,
but you have no choice.

340
00:19:22,167 --> 00:19:24,067
I'm all you have here
in the Philippines.

341
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:27,833
That's right,
I don't have a choice.

342
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,667
See, you are an idiot!

343
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,967
You really had to agree to that.

344
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,700
Bro..

345
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:39,033
How did you get away
from Hazel?

346
00:19:40,267 --> 00:19:41,700
So what can I help you with?

347
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:43,700
Do you need a job?

348
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:46,033
Yes, if you can help me
with that.

349
00:19:46,167 --> 00:19:48,367
Bro, that's easy.

350
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,933
I'll pass some work on to you.

351
00:19:50,067 --> 00:19:54,133
You know how to do electronics
repair, right?

352
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:55,033
Of course.

353
00:19:55,167 --> 00:19:57,300
There you go, that will be easy.

354
00:19:57,433 --> 00:19:58,900
Okay, I will help you.

355
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:01,433
But on one condition.

356
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,333
What is it?

357
00:20:03,467 --> 00:20:08,133
You can't call Felma
and your children.

358
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:11,333
To avoid World War 3.

359
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:22,467
And one more thing, Paz can't
find out that I've come here,

360
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,467
because it will be World War 4.

361
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,800
You know how Paz is.

362
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:28,333
She's basically competing
with Hazel

363
00:20:28,467 --> 00:20:31,633
for being the biggest war freak,
right?

364
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:34,800
How did we even get
to that topic? My goodness.

365
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:37,133
- Aren't we so kind?
- That's right.

366
00:20:37,933 --> 00:20:40,333
I told you so.

367
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:44,367
- Jessica, sweetie.
- Yes?

368
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:47,333
Can you buy us some drinks
and snacks outside?

369
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:48,767
I forgot to buy some.

370
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:50,267
What would you like?

371
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,967
You can get whatever is good.
It's up to you.

372
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:53,933
Thank you.

373
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:57,067
She's gotten so big.

374
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,300
So are you ready to drink?

375
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:00,733
Oh, yes.

376
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:01,733
Just a little, okay?

377
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:04,267
Yes, just a little.
Just two bottles.

378
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:09,533
Bro, tell me.
How did you get away from Hazel?

379
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:14,500
Here, open this bottle first.

380
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:25,700
Felma, check this out.

381
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:32,800
<i>Sisig ni Bunso
is getting good reviews!</i>

382
00:21:33,967 --> 00:21:36,867
But wait! There's more!
We have a lot of online orders.

383
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:42,800
We need to hire more people
to focus on our online orders!

384
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:44,767
Felma!

385
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:48,167
Felma, who are you talking to?

386
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:52,067
You are ruining my momentum!

387
00:21:54,067 --> 00:21:56,500
I said, who are you talking to?

388
00:21:56,633 --> 00:21:59,067
- Give that back!
- Jessica Cruz?

389
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:02,400
This is Manuel and Hazel's
daughter! Isn't she?

390
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:03,867
Give that back!

391
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:04,733
Paz!

392
00:22:04,867 --> 00:22:07,100
Hi, Miss Felma.

393
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:12,033
Philippine SIM card?
They're here in the Philippines?

394
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:16,867
Who else knows about this?
Are the kids aware of this?

395
00:22:19,167 --> 00:22:21,000
- Just Coleen.
- I see, just her.

396
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:22,100
So what are you planning to do?

397
00:22:22,233 --> 00:22:23,900
You're planning to meet
with him, aren't you?

398
00:22:24,033 --> 00:22:27,167
No! I don't have.
I don't have a plan.

399
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:30,067
No? So you don't have a plan,
right?

400
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,700
Nothing! There you go.

401
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:37,367
- What did you do?
- I deleted it.

402
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:41,600
So you won't be tempted to call
them or meet with them, right?

403
00:22:41,733 --> 00:22:43,667
You don't have the right
to do that, Paz.

404
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,400
I have a right! I'm your friend!

405
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:50,133
I'm just protecting you
from that bastard!

406
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:52,067
You are being too personal.

407
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,933
You shouldn't mess with this!

408
00:22:54,067 --> 00:22:55,000
Really?

409
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:56,767
Go ahead, you can get mad
at me all you want!

410
00:22:56,900 --> 00:23:00,567
But one of these days, Felma,
you will thank me for this.

411
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,567
I thank you!

412
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:04,400
Don't do this again.

413
00:23:04,533 --> 00:23:07,600
If you don't want to lose
your job and your friend!

414
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:25,200
Sweetie,
I have something to tell you.

415
00:23:27,933 --> 00:23:31,600
What do you know?
Tell me the truth.

416
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:35,000
What do you mean?

417
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:39,200
I heard that Manuel is back here
in the Philippines.

418
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:40,967
What?

419
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:42,233
Really?

420
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:48,567
Come on, Abel, don't try
to play dumb with me!

421
00:23:51,467 --> 00:23:53,067
Tell me the truth!

422
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,233
What do you know?

423
00:23:54,367 --> 00:23:56,100
Nothing! I don't know anything.

424
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:59,633
I just heard from you
that he got into an accident.

425
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:03,867
Are you telling the truth?

426
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,100
I know nothing!

427
00:24:06,233 --> 00:24:08,167
Fine, so what are you going
to tell me?

428
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:10,300
What is the latest?

429
00:24:11,167 --> 00:24:13,667
- It's Poldo.
- Oh, my!

430
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:17,400
Marisol caught him cheating,
so she threw him out!

431
00:24:17,533 --> 00:24:21,267
I knew it!
So where did she catch him?

432
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,400
Apparently,
it was in a beer house.

433
00:24:22,533 --> 00:24:24,100
Oh, my!

434
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,967
You're so stubborn, Coleen!

435
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:35,633
Didn't I tell you
not to call them anymore?

436
00:24:35,767 --> 00:24:37,967
Andrea! Give that back!

437
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:39,100
- Hello?
- Andrea!

438
00:24:39,233 --> 00:24:40,433
Jessica?

439
00:24:40,567 --> 00:24:42,467
Please stop communicating
with my sister!

440
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:44,400
We don't care about your father!

441
00:24:44,533 --> 00:24:45,500
Andrea!

442
00:24:45,633 --> 00:24:46,833
Stop!

443
00:24:48,667 --> 00:24:51,900
Tell your home-wrecker boss,
that flirty Felma,

444
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:54,000
that Hazel
Capistrano Cruz is here!

445
00:24:54,133 --> 00:24:55,833
How did she find you here?

446
00:24:55,967 --> 00:24:57,633
Our address is on our website.

447
00:24:57,767 --> 00:24:58,833
That's right!

448
00:24:58,967 --> 00:24:59,700
Hey, Felma!

449
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:01,300
This is what I'm talking about!

450
00:25:01,433 --> 00:25:04,567
Whenever Manuel is around,
it will only mean trouble!

451
00:25:04,733 --> 00:25:07,200
Come here, we have to talk!

452
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:08,333
You witch!

453
00:25:08,467 --> 00:25:10,800
If you touch me again,
I will gouge your eye out!

454
00:25:10,933 --> 00:25:13,667
I'm not your enemy, I'm an ally.

455
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:16,267
What made you think
that I need your help?

456
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:21,667
What if I tell you
that I can bring Manuel to you?

457
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,367
Hello, Jessica?

458
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:25,833
Can we meet?

459
00:25:31,033 --> 00:25:33,300
Dad, she's here.
